<BaseLayout title="About | Robert Otieno" description="About Robert Otieno, Enterprise Identity, Security & IT Operations Architect.">
	<section>
		<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
		<h1>Architecting Trust Infrastructure for Enterprise Systems</h1>
		<p class="lead">
			I work at the intersection of identity architecture, operational security, and privacy engineering to design resilient enterprise systems.
		</p>
		<p>
			My approach treats identity as infrastructure: access decisions must be measurable, governance must be operationally integrated, and privacy
			must be embedded into the architecture from the start.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Principles</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>Identity is the control plane for modern enterprise security.</li>
			<li>Operations translates policy into consistent execution.</li>
			<li>Privacy is a non-negotiable system constraint.</li>
			<li>Automation is required for scale and auditability.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Current Direction</h2>
		<p>
			I am focused on enterprise IAM modernization, access governance transformation, and practical pathways for decentralized identity in
			real-world organizations.
		</p>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>